{"id":1289585615,"question_id":3421,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1 week, 2 days","timestamp":1718505568,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"2 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1289585615/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Count Pairs That Form a Complete Day I","memory":"42.7 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public int countCompleteDayPairs(int[] hours) {\n        int res = 0;\n        Map<Integer, Integer> hs = new HashMap<>();\n        \n        for (int i=0; i<hours.length; i++) {\n            int rem = hours[i]%24;\n            int comp = (24-rem)%24;\n\n            if (hs.containsKey(comp)) {\n                res += hs.get(comp);\n            }\n\n            hs.put(rem, hs.getOrDefault(rem,0)+1);\n        }\n        \n        return res;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"count-pairs-that-form-a-complete-day-i","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
